People Tree,Ethical Fashion,DO NOT ORDER,"I've shopped with People Tree over the years and never had any problems... Until July 2023. I ordered 2 dresses but had to send them back because the fabric was really thin and they didn't fit properly. More Primark than People Tree quality. At the end of July, I noticed that the refund had not been processed and emailed People Tree. On July 31 I got a reply from the company Director, he said that their customer service specialist had had to leave the company at short notice and that “we are working through the backlog of outstanding issues as fast as we can to ensure that nothing gets missed whilst we recruit and train someone else.” Fast forward to September. A large letter landed on my doormat informing me that People Tree UK has collapsed into administration and listing me as one of the creditors. Unfortunately, I paid by debit card and never got my money back. The reason I’m posting this review is because I can see that their European website is still running and I saw two reviews from EU customers who ordered but never received anything. DO NOT ORDER!!! The European website hasn’t been updated for months. If you look at T&C’s, you’ll see that the website is operated by People Tree Ltd, a company registered in the UK under number 02949366, whereas orders are fulfilled by People Tree Enterprises BV, a company registered in The Netherlands under KVK 82275602. People Tree Ltd, registration number 02949366, is the company that entered administration last September. How can a company that is being liquidated operate a website and forward information about orders to the Dutch arm of People Tree? You can find Opus Restructuring Llp (their liquidator) details on Companies House should you wish to contact them. If you’re reading this and are EU based, please spread awareness so that unsuspecting customers wouldn’t be placing new orders on the Dutch website! On September 27, 2023 The Guardian wrote that “People Tree’s European website is continuing to operate, with a note promising that shipping to the UK will begin soon, but former insiders said the European operation’s only employee was being made redundant and it was not clear how trade would be able to continue as the buying and marketing had been run from the UK.”",1,2024-03-01 12:27:38+00:00,Trustpilot,ive shopped people tree year never problem july ordered dress send back fabric really thin didnt fit properly primark people tree quality end july noticed refund processed emailed people tree july got reply company director said customer service specialist leave company short notice working backlog outstanding issue fast ensure nothing get missed whilst recruit train someone else fast forward september large letter landed doormat informing people tree uk collapsed administration listing one creditor unfortunately paid debit card never got money back reason im posting review see european website still running saw two review eu customer ordered never received anything order european website hasnt updated month look tc youll see website operated people tree ltd company registered uk number whereas order fulfilled people tree enterprise bv company registered netherlands kvk people tree ltd registration number company entered administration last september company liquidated operate website forward information order dutch arm people tree find opus restructuring llp liquidator detail company house wish contact youre reading eu based please spread awareness unsuspecting customer wouldnt placing new order dutch website september guardian wrote people tree european website continuing operate note promising shipping uk begin soon former insider said european operation employee made redundant clear trade would able continue buying marketing run uk
